summary: Pixar's "Inside Out 2" has recently been released on Disney+, marking the latest installment in the animated franchise. However, others have praised its streaming availability, acknowledging the anticipation surrounding its release. Additionally, the film's exploration of emotions has sparked interest in the scientific basis behind these concepts. Despite the controversy, "Inside Out 2" has generated discussions among fans and critics alike, with some expressing concerns over its portrayal of LGBT+ representation.

name: Julie Chrisley resentencing
summary: Reality TV star Julie Chrisley has been resentenced to seven years in prison for bank fraud and tax evasion. The sentence was upheld after a previous 84-month sentence was reduced on appeal. Chrisley made an emotional plea at her court appearance, but the judge ultimately decided to maintain the original sentence. Despite the reduction, Chrisley will continue to serve her sentence. The resentencing comes after Chrisley and her husband Todd were convicted of multiple financial crimes in 2022. The couple has maintained their innocence and is currently appealing their convictions.
